  "dmConversation" : {
    "conversationId" : "52522040-141018504",
    "messages" : [ {
      "messageCreate" : {
        "recipientId" : "52522040",
        "text" : "Keith, I‚Äôve never been to Crete (and neither have I had the pleasure of meeting Maria!) so I promise to look you up if I ever do get there.  I‚Äôm still with the FCO and am currently responsible for our corporate operations overseas (bricks and mortar, logistics, moving people and their families around the world).  The MSc is part of my development plan - although also motivated by thoughts about what I may do when I retire (which due to luck of timing will be in only 14 years).  I‚Äôm hoping to write a dissertation on how the development and implementation of a national security and foreign policy could be improved with the application of some systemic thought.  I still see quite a lot of the philosophers from my year (we tend to gather once a year or so).  I‚Äôm in touch with Alice electronically but haven‚Äôt seen her for a few years.  Alexis has recently had some children and is juggling career (she‚Äôs involved with some youth development projects) and family.  You may know Michael Garnett (writing on free will at Birkbeck now) and Carrie Jenkins (Vancouver I think) and I see Keith Allen (York) from time to time.  I turn up to Robinson events from time to time (annual reception this year at the House of Commons so I will be there).  I hope we have a chance to catch up at some point and do let me know if you‚Äôre passing through London (although I‚Äôve now moved to the countryside with wife and two children I am in Westminster most days).  Best wishes to you, Daniel",
        "mediaUrls" : [ ],
        "senderId" : "141018504",
        "id" : "1143777982546399237",
        "createdAt" : "2019-06-26T07:08:16.105Z"
      }
    }, {
      "messageCreate" : {
        "recipientId" : "141018504",
        "text" : "Hello Daniel -- \nWell 'Frankish' isn't a common name (except in East Yorkshire), so it's not too hard to be the best-known Frankish in a particular field! \nIt's great to hear from you again. What are you up to these days? Are you still working in Whitehall or is the MSc part of a career change? \nDo you keep in touch with many people from Robinson? I still hear from a few (Alice M, who has gone on to great things in philosophy; Ricky J who is an academic in China ...). \nI'm living in Crete these days, with my family (did you ever meet Maria?) Do let us know if you ever visit the island. It would be lovely to meet up again. Very best wishes, Keith",
        "mediaUrls" : [ ],
        "senderId" : "52522040",
        "id" : "1143553928052842500",
        "createdAt" : "2019-06-25T16:17:57.379Z"
      }
    }, {
      "messageCreate" : {
        "recipientId" : "52522040",
        "text" : "Dear Keith, hope all is well with you.  A quick note to let you know that - in the process of studying for an MSc in Systems Thinking in Practice - my module material has just quotes from ‚ÄúEvans and Frankish 2009‚Äù - in discussing different modes of cognition and their impact on systemic thinking about ‚Äúmessy‚Äù situations.  I was pleased to discover that there is only one Frankish intellectually roaming around cognitive science! With best wishes, Daniel",
        "mediaUrls" : [ ],
        "senderId" : "141018504",
        "id" : "1143460003866730500",
        "createdAt" : "2019-06-25T10:04:44.084Z"
      }
    } ]
  }
