  "dmConversation" : {
    "conversationId" : "52522040-1485357409",
    "messages" : [ {
      "messageCreate" : {
        "recipientId" : "52522040",
        "text" : "I appreciate your generosity in responding. \n\nI wasn't aware of the broader context either. \n\nHonestly, I didn't realize that anything was genuinely \"taboo\" these days... The mere existence of a taboo makes me want to interrogate and examine it. Though, I imagine you probably feel differently, having just been put through the wringer.",
        "mediaUrls" : [ ],
        "senderId" : "1485357409",
        "id" : "1231025171487744005",
        "createdAt" : "2020-02-22T01:17:26.920Z"
      }
    }, {
      "messageCreate" : {
        "recipientId" : "1485357409",
        "text" : "One reason it was stupid is that I should have realized that the topic is taboo -- perhaps for very good reasons. There was also a context I should have known  about (the furore over Dawkins's tweet and the UK government's appointment of someone who who had made controversial comments about eugenics.) It should also have made clear my intentions in asking the question. As for the apology, I made it because I was told that I'd upset some people, and I genuinely regretted doing that, even unintentionally.",
        "mediaUrls" : [ ],
        "senderId" : "52522040",
        "id" : "1230987012984975370",
        "createdAt" : "2020-02-21T22:45:49.235Z"
      }
    }, {
      "messageCreate" : {
        "recipientId" : "52522040",
        "text" : "Hi Keith, \n\nI have learned a lot from following your Twitter conversations over time. Thank you for sharing your thoughts on this mess of a platform.\n\nI know that you would like to put the debacle of your question about eugenics behind you, so please forgive me for asking one further question... I think that maybe there's still something for us all to learn here. There are so many people who still do not understand why your question elicited the very strong responses we saw. I count myself among this group. \n\nIf you really came to see this tweet as \"stupid,\" I'd love to understand why. I think we would all benefit.\n\nIf on the other hand, you have apologized because you felt bullied into an apology (I would have!) ‚Äî wouldn't that be something interesting for public intellectual such as yourself to think aloud about?",
        "mediaUrls" : [ ],
        "senderId" : "1485357409",
        "id" : "1230923758774497284",
        "createdAt" : "2020-02-21T18:34:28.304Z"
      }
    } ]
  }
