        "text" : "Hello Keith! I'm a professional visual designer with a lot of experience in editorial design (and an amateur Dennettian philosopher) and I'd recommend going with a designed layout for readability. There are many typographic parameters we adjust for a better reading experience, like typeface choice, point size, leading, line length, etc. and the manuscript format isn't a good choice regarding many of these parameters. I'd love to help if you need it. We normally work in Adobe Indesign for multipage documents (which has lots of advantages and shortcuts for typesetting); I can set the articles there and give you the PDFs, or I can create a template for you to use. Or, I can at least give some general feedback on typography for whatever software you're using. Cheers!",
